<div id="protein"><h3> 41g</h3> </div>
</div>

<div id= "ingredienthdr">
<h1>Ingredients</h1>
</div>

<div id="ingredients">
<div id="ingredientone"><img src="/images/chickenlegs.jpeg"/> 2 chicken legs</div>
<div id="ingredienttwo"><img src="/images/anchovies.jpeg"/>2 anchovies</div>
<div id="ingredienttwo"><img src="/images/basil.jpeg"/>2 sprigs basil</div>
<div id="ingredientfour"><img src="/images/parsley.jpeg"/>1/8 bunch parsley</div>
</div>

<div id="ingredients">
<div id="ingredientone"><img src="/images/cilantro.jpeg"/>1/8 bunch cilantro</div>
<div id="ingredienttwo"><img src="/images/tarragon.jpeg"/>1 sprig tarragon</div>
<div id="ingredientthree"><img src="/images/arugula.jpeg"/>1 handful arugula</div>
<div id="ingredientfour"><img src="/images/2garlic.jpeg"/>2 cloves garlic</div>
</div>

<div id="ingredients">
<div id="ingredientone"><img src="/images/meyerlemon.jpeg"/>1 meyer lemon</div>
<div id="ingredienttwo"><img src="/images/goldpotatoes.jpeg"/>3/4 lb gold potatoes</div>
<div id="ingredientthree"><img src="/images/capers.jpeg"/>3 tbsp capers</div>
</div>

<div id= "equipmenthdr">
<h1>Equipment</h1>
</div>

<div id="equipment">
<div id="equipmentone"><a href=""><img src="/images/foodprocessor.jpeg"/>food processor</a></div>
<div id="equipmenttwo"><a href=""><img src="/images/bakingsheet.jpeg"/>2 baking sheets</a></div>
</div>

<div id="preparation">
<h1>Preparation</h1>
</div>

<div id="instruction">
<div id="image"><img src="/images/polloalforno1.jpeg"/> </div>
<div id="step">Move one rack to the upper portion of the oven, and another rack to bottom. Preheat the oven to 425Ëš.
<p>Place the chicken legs on the roasting pan or baking sheet.</p>
<p>Cut the meyer lemon in half and squeeze the juice of each lemon half onto each chicken leg. Coat with a generous amount of ground pepper and sprinkle a pinch of salt over each leg. Place the squeezed meyer lemon halves in the pan cut-side down.</p></div>
</div>

<div id="instruction">
<div id="image"><img src="/images/polloalforno2.jpeg"/> </div>
<div id="step">Place on the top rack of the oven and roast for 40 minutes.
<p>During the last 5 minutes of roasting, raise the heat to broil, to give the chicken a crispy skin.</p></div>
</div>

<div id="instruction">
<div id="image"><img src="/images/polloalforno3.jpeg"/> </div>
<div id="step"><i>While the chicken roasts, assemble the salsa verde.</i> Place the cilantro, arugula, basil, parsley, tarragon, capers, anchovies, and garlic in the bowl of the food processor with 3 tbsp of olive oil and a pinch of salt. Set aside for plating.</div>
</div>

<div id="instruction">
<div id="image"><img src="/images/polloalforno4.jpeg"/> </div>
<div id="step">Cut the potatoes in quarters. 
<p>Place the potatoes on a roasting pan or baking sheet and toss with olive oil. Move them to the bottom rack of the oven and roast for 25 minutes.</p></div>
</div>

<div id="instruction">
<div id="image"><img src="/images/polloalforno5.jpeg"/> </div>
<div id="step">Sauce the plate, and lay the chicken leg on top. Accent with the roasted potatoes.</div>
</div>


